msgid "Chapter contents"
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/index.rst:5
msgid "File share management"
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/index.rst:7
msgid ""
"UCS supports the central management of directory shares. A share "
"registered via the UMC module :guilabel:`Shares` is created on an "
"arbitrary UCS server system as part of the UCS domain replication."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/index.rst:11
msgid ""
"Provision for accessing clients can occur via CIFS (supported by "
"Windows/Linux clients) and/or NFS (primarily supported by Linux/Unix). "
"The NFS shares managed in the UMC module can be mounted by clients both "
"via NFSv3 and via NFSv4."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/index.rst:15
msgid ""
"If a file share is deleted on a server, the shared files in the directory"
" are preserved."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/index.rst:18
msgid ""
"To be able to use access control lists on a share, the underlying Linux "
"file system must support POSIX ACLs. In UCS the file systems ``ext4`` and"
" ``XFS`` support POSIX ACLs. The Samba configuration also allows storing "
"DOS file attributes in extended attributes of the Unix file system. To "
"use extended attributes, the partition must be mounted using the mount "
"option ``user_xattr``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/msdfs.rst:4
msgid "Support for MSDFS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/msdfs.rst:6
msgid ""
"The Microsoft Distributed File System (MSDFS) is a distributed file "
"system which makes it possible to access shares spanning several servers "
"and paths as a virtual directory hierarchy. The load can then be "
"distributed across several servers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/msdfs.rst:11
msgid ""
"Setting the *MSDFS Root* option for a share (see :ref:`shares-"
"management`) indicates that the shared directory is a share which can be "
"used for the MSDFS. References to other shares are only displayed in such"
" an MSDFS root, elsewhere they are hidden."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/msdfs.rst:16
msgid ""
"To be able to utilize the functions of a distributed file system, the "
"|UCSUCRV| :envvar:`samba/enable-msdfs` has to be set to ``yes`` on a file"
" server. Afterwards Samba has to be restarted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/msdfs.rst:20
msgid ""
"For creating a reference named :file:`tofb` from server ``sa`` within the"
" share :file:`fa` to share :file:`fb` on the server ``sb``, the following"
" command has to be executed in directory :file:`fa`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/msdfs.rst:24
msgid "$ ln -s msdfs:sb\\\\fb tofb"
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/msdfs.rst:28
msgid ""
"This reference will be displayed on every client capable of MSDFS (e.g. "
"*Windows 2000* and *Windows XP*) as a regular directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/msdfs.rst:33
msgid ""
"Only restricted user groups should have write access to root directories."
" Otherwise, it would be possible for users to redirect references to "
"other shares, and intercept or manipulate files. In addition, paths to "
"the shares, as well as the references are to be spelled entirely in lower"
" case. If changes are made in the references, the concerned clients have "
"to be restarted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/msdfs.rst:40
msgid ""
"Further information on this issue can be found in :cite:t:`samba3-howto-"
"chapter-20`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/quota.rst:4
msgid "Configuration of file system quota"
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/quota.rst:6
msgid ""
"UCS allows the limiting of the storage space available to a user on a "
"partition. These thresholds can be set as either a quantity of storage "
"space (e.g., 500 MB per user) or a maximum number of files without a "
"defined size limit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/quota.rst:11
msgid "Two types of thresholds are differentiated:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/quota.rst:15
msgid "Hard limit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/quota.rst:14
msgid ""
"The *hard limit* is the maximum storage space a user can employ. If it is"
" attained, no further files can be saved."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/quota.rst:23
msgid "Soft limit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/quota.rst:18
msgid ""
"If the *soft limit* is attained - which must be smaller than the hard "
"limit - and the storage space used is still below the hard limit, the "
"user is given a grace period of seven days to delete unused data. Once "
"seven days have elapsed, it is no longer possible to save or change "
"additional files. A warning is displayed to users who access a file "
"system with an exceeded quota via CIFS (the threshold is based on the "
"soft limit)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/quota.rst:25
msgid ""
"If a quota value of ``0`` has been configured, it is evaluated as an "
"unlimited quota."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/quota.rst:28
msgid ""
"Quotas can either be defined via the UMC module :guilabel:`Filesystem "
"quotas` or a policy for shares, see :ref:`shares-quota-policy`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/quota.rst:31
msgid ""
"File system quotas can only be applied on partitions with the file "
"systems ``ext4`` and ``XFS``. Before file system quotas can be "
"configured, the use of file system quotas needs to be activated per "
"partition, see :ref:`shares-quota-umc`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/quota.rst:39
msgid "Activating file system quota"
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/quota.rst:41
msgid ""
"In the UMC module :guilabel:`Filesystem quotas`, all the partitions are "
"listed on which quotas can be set up. Only partitions are shown which are"
" currently mounted under a mount point."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/quota.rst:50
msgid "The UMC module *File system quotas*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/quota.rst:50
msgid "The UMC module :guilabel:`File system quotas`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/quota.rst:52
msgid ""
"The current quota status (activated/deactivated) is shown and can be "
"changed with *Activate* and *Deactivate*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/quota.rst:55
msgid ""
"If quota has been activated on a ``XFS`` root-partition, the system has "
"to be rebooted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/quota.rst:61
msgid "Configuring file system quota"
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/quota.rst:63
msgid ""
"Quotas can either be defined via the UMC module :guilabel:`Filesystem "
"quotas` or a policy for shares, see :ref:`central-policies`. The "
"configuration through a policy allows setting a default value for all "
"users, while the UMC module allows configuration of user-specific quota "
"values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/quota.rst:68
msgid ""
"The user-specific quota settings can be configured with the UMC module "
":guilabel:`Filesystem quotas`. The permitted storage quantities can be "
"set with the pencil symbol for all enabled partitions. All the settings "
"are set user-specifically. :guilabel:`Add` can be used to set the "
"thresholds for soft and hard limits for a user."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/quota.rst:74
msgid ""
"The quota settings can also be set with a *User quota* share policy. The "
"settings apply for all users of a share; it is not possible to establish "
"different quota limits for different users within one policy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/quota.rst:78
msgid ""
"Quota settings that are applied via a quota policy are by default only "
"applied once to the file system. If the setting is changed, it will not "
"be applied automatically on the next user login. To inherit changed quota"
" values, the option *Reapply settings on every login* can be activated at"
" the quota policy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/quota.rst:83
msgid ""
"Quota policies can only be used on partitions for which the quota support"
" is enabled in the UMC module, see :ref:`shares-quota-umc`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/quota.rst:88
msgid ""
"File system quotas always apply to a full partition. Even if the policies"
" are defined for shares, they are used on complete partitions. If, for "
"example, three shares are provided on one server which are all saved on "
"the separate :file:`/var/` partition and three different policies are "
"configured and used, the most restrictive setting applies for the "
"complete partition. If different quotas are used, it is recommended to "
"distribute the data over individual partitions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/quota.rst:99
msgid "Evaluation of quota during login"
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/quota.rst:101
msgid ""
"The settings defined in the UCS management system are evaluated and "
"enabled during login to UCS systems by the tool :command:`univention-"
"user-quota` run in the PAM stack."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/quota.rst:105
msgid ""
"If no quota are needed, the evaluation can be disabled by setting the "
"|UCSUCRV| :envvar:`quota/userdefault` to ``no``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../shares/quota.rst:108
msgid ""
"If the |UCSUCRV| :envvar:`quota/logfile` is set to any filename, the "
"activation of the quotas is logged in the specified file."
msgstr ""

